Change alone a helix

Find the derivative of f(x, y, z) = x² + y² + z² in the direction
of the unit tangent vector of the helix

r(t) = (cos t)i + (sin t)j + tk

at the point where t = -pi/4, 0, and pi/4. The function f gives
the square of the distance from a point P(x, y, z) on the helix to
the origin. The derivative calculated here give the rates at whitch
the square of the distance is changing with respect to t as P moves 
through the points where t = -pi/4, 0, and pi


fx = 2x, fy = 2y, fz = 2z

∇f = 2x i + 2y j + 2z k = (2cos t)i + (2sin t)j + 2t k

v = dr/dt = (-sin t)i + (cos t)j + k
|v| = sqrt(sin²t + cos²t + 1) = sqrt(2)
u = v/|v| = ((-sin t)i + (cos t)j + k)/sqrt(2)


proj∇f = dot(∇f, u) = (-2sin t cos t + 2 sin t cos t + 2t)/sqrt(2) = 2t/sqrt(2)

so proj∇f(-pi/4) = -pi/2sqrt(2), (0) = 0, (pi) = 2pi/sqrt(2)


xoozi 这题比较有意思, 不去求各点的u, 和∇f, 而是代数地全部计算后化简, 我一开始也想岔了





